{
  "text": "In expectation, we will see that each difference term qw i j \u2212 Eqw i j that appears in the product contributes a factor of n \u22121/2 , and thus that the magnitude of (17) is at most O(n \u2212l/2 ). To show this, we require the ability to estimate moments of the terms that appear in the right hand side of [CITATION_1] . This is expressed in the following lemma.",
